title: Parking Violation Citation Question
text:
Hey all, I'm fairly new in town and I'm still getting familiar with a lot in the city. 

I parked in a spot yesterday that had a "No Parking Anytime" sign posted that I did not see. 

I was gone for about an hour and I got a ticket. 

The ticket itself wasn't a big deal and I already paid for it. But my question about some comments the officer left on the ticket 

It says: "Impound. No Parking Anytime. Picture Taken." 

What does that comment mean exactly? Is my car due to be towed? 

Thanks
